reviewText: Music and dance at it's best!
The music, the dance, the enthusiasm and professionalism of this young ensemble.  Absolutely breathtaking!  So....when are they coming to Syracuse, NY???
I love the mixture of music from other countries. The dancing is superb,I don't get tired of watching. Amazon allways deliver
I really liked the dancing in this DVD.  They put on a really good show with a variety of dance types.

As the title of this says,this is recommended for those interested in a variety of dance styles since this features African, Latin and Irish Step. Fans of "Riverdance" will enjoy this production because not only does it involve Irish step dancing, this production was produced by the same crew that did "Riverdance".
A troupe of talented dancers and musicians present a stunning program of Irish dance, Latin and African rhythms. For anyone who enjoys contemporary dance.
love this show. i wish that i could see it in person and not just on the dvd, but they did not tour for very long.

The eclecticism of the music and dance really make this production stand out, and the way the musical genres morph into one another is a bit of genius. The dancers are superlative and even the scenery gets justifiable applause. This is not a "watch it once and store it on the shelf" purchase. And it is, for me, better as a purchase rather than a rental.
Enjoyed the show very much!  Hope it comes to the Twin Cities in MN!
Wonderful DVD with so many talented dancers and singers - will enjoy again and again.
Very disappointing performances  - similar stye to Riverdance but not as appealing to me with smaller grouping and non-celtic content for me
picture quality and recording was terrible
Got this for my mother for her 75th b-day - She used to be a dance instructor- i saw this on PBS & knew I had to get it for her - she's enjoyed Riverdance in the past
